wikipedia_page.main: Dr John Alexander Smith  (June 1818–17 August 1883) was a 19th-century Scottish physician, antiquarian, archaeologist and ornithologist.

response: John Alexander Smith (21 April 1863 – 19 December 1939) was a British idealist philosopher, who was the Jowett Lecturer of philosophy at Balliol College, Oxford from 1896 to 1910, and Waynflete Professor of Moral and Metaphysical Philosophy, carrying a Fellowship at Magdalen College in the same university, from 1910 to 1936. He was born in Dingwall and died in Oxford.
*John Alexander Smith (physician) (1818–1883), Scottish physician, antiquarian, archaeologist and ornithologist
In 1882 he was elected a Fellow of the Royal Society of Edinburgh. His proposers were Thomas Sprague, Dr John Alexander Smith, William Thomson, Lord Kelvin, and James Sanderson.
